s6 is [[Article description::a package that provides a [[daemontools|daemontools-inspired]] process supervision suite, a notification framework, a UNIX domain super-server, and tools for file descriptor holding and suidless privilege gain]]. It can be used as an init system component, and also as a helper for supervising [[OpenRC]] services. A high level overview of s6 is available [https://www.skarnet.org/software/s6/overview.html here]. The package's documentation is provided in HTML format, and can be read on a text user interface using for example [https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/www-client/links www-client/links].

