==== From sysvinit ====

The s6 package provides a script called {{C|s6-svscanboot}}, that can be launched and supervised by [https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/sys-apps/sysvinit sysvinit] by adding a 'respawn' line for it in {{Path|/etc/inittab}}<ref>[https://www.skarnet.org/software/s6/s6-svscan-not-1.html How to run s6-svscan under another init process]. Retrieved on July 16th, 2017.</ref>. It is an execline script that launches an {{C|s6-svscan}} process, with its standard output and error redirected to {{Path|/service/s6-svscan-log/fifo}}. This allows setting up a FIFO and a logger program to log messages sent by supervision tree processes to {{C|s6-svscan}}'s standard output and error, with the the same technique used by [[s6 and s6-rc based init system]]s. {{C|s6-svscan}}'s standard input will be redirected to {{Path|/dev/null}}. The enviroment will be emptied and then set according to the contents of environment directory {{Path|/service/.s6-svscan/env}}, if it exists, with an {{C|s6-envdir}} invocation. The scan directory will be {{Path|/service}}.

{{C|s6-svscanboot}} is provided as an example; it is the {{Path|examples/s6-svscanboot}} file in the package's {{Path|/usr/share/doc}} subdirectory. Users that want this setup will need to copy (and possibly uncompress) the script to {{Path|/bin}}, manually edit {{Path|/etc/inittab}}, and then call {{C|telinit}}:
{{FileBox|filename=/etc/inittab|1=SV:12345:respawn:/bin/s6-svscanboot}}

{{RootCmd|telinit q}}

{{Warning|The {{C|s6-svscanboot}} provided by s6 version 2.6.0.0 and earlier doesn't handle environment directory {{Path|/service/.s6-svscan/env}} correctly. A working script exists in the package's [https://git.skarnet.org/cgi-bin/cgit.cgi/s6/plain/examples/s6-svscanboot current Git HEAD], and should be used instead.}}

This will make sysvinit launch and supervise {{C|s6-svscan}} when entering runlevels 1 to 5. Because s6 and execline programs used in the script and invoked using absolute pathnames are asumed to be in directory {{Path|/command}}, a symlink to the correct path for Gentoo must be created: 
{{RootCmd|ln -s bin /command}}

An s6 service directory for the {{C|s6-svscan}} logger can be created with the {{C|s6-linux-init-maker}} program from package [https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/sys-apps/s6-linux-init s6-linux-init]:
{{RootCmd|s6-envuidgid user s6-linux-init-maker -l /service -U temp|cp -a temp/run-image/{service/s6-svscan-log,uncaught-logs} /service}}

The logger will be an {{C|s6-log}} process that logs to directory {{Path|/service/uncaught-logs}}, prepending messages with a timestamp in [https://cr.yp.to/libtai/tai64.html external TAI64N format]. Username ''user'' should be replaced by a valid account's username, to allow {{C|s6-log}} to run as an unprivileged process, and {{Path|temp}} will be a temporary directory created by {{C|s6-linux-init-maker}} on the working directory, that can be removed once the necessary subdirectories are copied to {{Path|/service}}.
